With last night’s shoot, I officially completed my AFI admissions package. 
Thank you to my amazing friends who helped make this happen. You all are a blessing! ❤️
Now I’m off to the editing room 🤓

I’m excited to announce that my director’s reel is finally out! 🎥

I’m a director and filmmaker based in Los Angeles - and I’m thrilled to share my work with you all.

Take a look at my reel and let me know what you think! I’m always looking for new projects and collaborations, so if you have an idea, I’d love to hear it. 😁
.
.
.
#filmmaker #filmdirector #latinofilmmaker #indiefilmmaking #shortfilms

We are so excited to announce that Daddy was selected as the best student film at the LGBTQ+ Toronto Film Festival! 🎉 

We owe tp and crew. It was a team effort to bring our story to life and make this dream a reality. 

We would like to thank the Toronto Film Festival for selecting us and recognizing our hard work. We are truly honored! 🙏 

We look forward to hearing what the critics have to say and we invite everyone to check out the reviews. 

Let’s celebrate this moment and keep making amazing films! 🎬

🎉Congrats to my talented friend and cinematographer, Allyson Estrada and her amazing team! Your tireless hard work and exceptional talent has been recognized with this nomination. It’s an incredible accomplishment and I am so proud of you all! 
.
.
#cinematography #filmfestival #shortfilms #shortfilmfestival
